column5: Wow! all those videos are incredible!  All we need is HD helmet cam video of some extreme angling!
The smart ones were harnessed in, but the guy with the camera and the guy in front of him near the end weren't.
Nobody else noticed that Solo was there too (check at 6:12)? That guy has been everywhere!!
That'll get ya puckered up for sure.  Forget the guys walkin it...............Id like to meet the guys that BUILT it
I was thinking the same thing! that's all concrete.  I'd fall and die within three steps.
There were guys on the trail who were harnessed but our guy the camera toting dude was not harnessed.  Insane.
Walkin  a sidewalk in TO was more dangerous than that this evening....

I've enjoyed all the links so far.  There is nothing like getting high on the job.  http://www.liveleak.com/mp53/player.swf?config=http://www.liveleak.com/mp53/player_config.php?token=07b_1284580365%26embed=1

no thanks... i choose life!  im terrified of heights... i started shaking just watching that. when he looked down while going across that little beam.... with te pointy rocks 26725836 feet below... i peed myself a little.
~~~~check out this site, then go change your pants  http://www.angelfire.com/ak2/intelligencerreport/scariest_path.html
woooow.. when he walked on that little beam cause the path is broken is crazy.  Not unless my life depended on it.
absolutely insane! I want to try it!  Anyone else wondering what the fishing's like in the waters below?
WOW
INSANE!
HMMMMM, looks like they may have been neglecting some maintenance on that pathway.
OMG......... i couldnt watch the whole thing.I was getting vertigo.Insane for sure.
The harnesses totally compromise the experience
Now that is cool.  The filmer is definately balsy to not be clipped in and walking all that with a camera.
Amazing, thanks for sharing that!! Awesome!!!!!
Awesome!  Even scarier, check out this downhill race from the same web page!  Chile Race
NUTS!!!  Gimme 2 minutes....
Holy snikies
My training wheels would never hold up on the stairs.
No Way, that is sweet.  I loved that vid.  I would do both the trail and the bike, but the bike has me jazzed, common spring!!!!
woah... i still feel queezie
never, ever, everevereverever would i even consider that...those guys have some giant cahones
Its all in what you're used to, and I'm going to have bad dreams tonight
Or maybe a nice scenic trail ride on your dirt bike.  Scenic Trail Ride
LOL wow that's crazy I would like to do that just for the view some of those mountain faces were amazing.
the dog in the bike race also has some nerve

The bike one is really cool too, although a fall there might be a broken arm/ribs some bruises (or nothing at all).  The fact that if you slip walking across a 4" beam hundreds of feet in the air just to take in some cool views freaks me out more for sure.  If the bridge crumbles or you slip you die lol
it looked like they were harnessed in...at one point i saw i guy with a harness clip off that cable that runs along the mountain wall but either way, like i said, never ever ever.......
Yea the bike video is neat but really it's no worst then doing downhill biking through the forest. But it is still a great video and a decent run that they have there.
Same thing here Paul. I had to turn it off half way through. I'll watch the rest when I'm safe in bed.
